headline: Does Chevron's (CVX) Renewed Venezuelan Oil Access and LNG Deal Reshape Its Supply Strategy?
summary: In late August, two Chevron-chartered tankers delivered Venezuelan crude to US waters after the company received a restricted license from the Treasury, while Chevron's subsidiary signed a 10-year agreement to supply liquefied natural gas to China's ENN LNG Trading Company Limited.
